cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.DM. 

The paper proposes a framework for combining linear programs and logic programs, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of logical concepts of objects, relations, and quantified variables suggests that the paper may also be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the experiments on approximate inference, solving Markov decision processes, and collective inference suggest that the paper may also be relevant to data mining (cs.DM).
